publishedfiledetails.title: Checkpoint Block
publishedfiledetails.file_description:
Block that checkpoints your progress. Or the mapstart if no checkpoint blck has been touched yet.
Resets you when the reset block is touched. The reset point is the bottom center of the block.

If you don't want the to be reset to the start and just reset once at least one checkpoint has been touched use the level tag:
CheckpointsIgnoreStart

Checkpoint RGB: 1, 238, 124
Reset RGB: 2, 238, 124

Only a single pixel of the checkpoint should be placed.
The checkpoint block should NOT be placed against a wall as the King potentially will be inside the wall on reset.
To provide your own texture for the checkpoint a checkpoint.xnb should be placed inside your maps folder (next to the level at the root level of the map folder).

publishedfiledetails.title: Custom wind switch
publishedfiledetails.file_description:
The mod allows you to customise the 2 ways wind block behaviour.

In the level_settings.xml file, in the Tags scope, just add the following line (or add a Worldsmith tag):

<Tags>
    <string>CustomWindSwitch=(1,2,2),(2,12.5,5,0,2)</string>
</Tags>

On this example, for screen 1 you will get 2 seconds left, 2 seconds right.
And for screen 2, you will get 12.5 seconds of no wind, and 5 seconds of 2 times base velocity wind.

It is a list (delimited by ',') of tuple.

Parameters of the tuple:
- (int) screen index: the screen index where the wind block is (first screen is 1).
- (float) left time: the time of the wind block blowing left.
- (float) right time: the time of the wind block blowing right. 
For custom velocity, you need to provide both sides.
- (optional float) left velocity: multiplier on the base velocity of the wind (base depend on the wind block you put on the map).
- (optional float) right velocity: same as prev.

You need to add the 2 ways wind blocks inside the level.xnb file, on the corresponding screens.

Github repo: https://github.com/elmousse/jk-custom-wind-switch-time

publishedfiledetails.title: Mirror Mode
publishedfiledetails.file_description:
[quote=Mirrored Map by Lavamander, KampZu & Mican]"The better you knew the original map, the more this will confuse your brain." [/quote]

Do you remember the "Mirrored Map" from the JumpKingPlus days? Now, you can relive the fun through "Mirror mode"!

Mirror Mode lets you experience the entire game with the visuals flipped horizontally, giving you a new way to "enjoy" the game. This mod achieves the mirrored effect by flipping the rendered visuals. Here are the features:
[list]
    [*]Keeping the game logic identical to the original Jump King.
    [*]Can be toggle in both main menu and ingame pause menu.
    [*]NPC dialogues, ending credits, and level names display correctly without being mirrored.
    [*]Supports all maps. (Of course including custom maps on workshop!)
    [*]Can also mirror babe art now! (11/15/2024)
[/list]

You can find the source code [url=https://github.com/JeFi-314/JumpKing-MirrorMode]here[/url]

publishedfiledetails.title: Conveyor Block
publishedfiledetails.file_description:
A conveyor block acts like a conveyor belt gimmick (also maintaining the player's momentum when he exits it).

### Color codes
R : Always 255
G : 100 for moving right, 101 for left
B : 1 to 16 for speed (1/2 pixel per frame step)

For info, king walks at 1.5px per frame, and side jump is 3.5px.

Don't hesitate to give feedback to help improve the mod, and enjoy making awesome custom maps with the mod!

Thanks to the JK modding community for helping me during the creation of my first mod!

Github repo if you wanna take a look at it or found an issue : https://github.com/elmousse/JKConveyorBlockMod
